  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6763.1 sitting above the max negative gamma strike at 6750 (-61.1B), dealers are currently short gamma and forced to buy this rally, creating amplifying pressure that's driving price toward the 6800 positive gamma wall where they'll flip to selling. The massive negative GEX concentration between 6745-6765 creates a volatile zone where any pullback will trigger aggressive dealer buying, while the recent wall break and GEX surge indicate momentum is building for a test of 6800 resistance. Key levels: defend 6750 for continued upside momentum, break below 6745 for potential flush lower, and watch 6800 as the critical flip point where dealer flow reverses.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect volatile upside push toward 6800 with strong support around 6750.",
